</node>
<node id="Down Syndrome">
  <data key="d0">Down Syndrome</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Down syndrome is a genetic disorder that is associated with diabetes.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-12fe828372a20b6606e010f0fd5e6263</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770136309</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Taiwan">
  <data key="d0">Taiwan</data>
  <data key="d1">location</data>
  <data key="d2">Taiwan is the location where a recent study indicated the rising prevalence of type 2 diabetes in children.&lt;SEP&gt;Taiwan is the location of a study that identified type 2 diabetes as a leading cause of diabetes in children aged 6-18 years.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-12fe828372a20b6606e010f0fd5e6263&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-42a410eaaaed4b7428f5e95a4c7c4580</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770136309</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Eastern Mediterranean Region">
  <data key="d0">Eastern Mediterranean Region</data>
  <data key="d1">location</data>
  <data key="d2">The Eastern Mediterranean Region is experiencing increasing rates of diabetes mellitus and associated health issues.&lt;SEP&gt;The Eastern Mediterranean Region spans from Pakistan in the east to Morocco in the west and features varied ethnic groups and high diabetes prevalence rates.&lt;SEP&gt;The Eastern Mediterranean Region includes various countries with high diabetes prevalence rates among the top ten globally.&lt;SEP&gt;The Eastern Mediterranean Region is where screening for type 2 diabetes in children over 10 is recommended based on specific criteria.&lt;SEP&gt;The Eastern Mediterranean Region is noted for a rising prevalence of type 2 diabetes among its populations.&lt;SEP&gt;The Eastern Mediterranean Region is mentioned as a location where diabetic nephropathy is a common health issue affecting patients.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-12fe828372a20b6606e010f0fd5e6263&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5384df975133ef2a52113cd3ca0f897e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d8c827cc2249067692290d6a8a0e8018&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-eb1bc7614fcd68decf9461b3b6290e95&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f15f59b3ff05825a61f252ed8f9a74e1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5e1400e1158e4f7be2283a0366ebf4f2</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770136309</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Polycystic Ovarian Syndrome">
  <data key="d0">Polycystic Ovarian Syndrome</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Polycystic ovarian syndrome is a condition associated with insulin resistance.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-12fe828372a20b6606e010f0fd5e6263&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-eb1bc7614fcd68decf9461b3b6290e95</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770136310</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Gestational Diabetes">
  <data key="d0">Gestational Diabetes</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Gestational diabetes is a type of diabetes that occurs during pregnancy and has implications for both maternal and fetal health.&lt;SEP&gt;Gestational diabetes is a condition of carbohydrate intolerance with hyperglycemia occurring during pregnancy.&lt;SEP&gt;Gestational Diabetes is a temporary form of diabetes that can occur during pregnancy, requiring careful management.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-12fe828372a20b6606e010f0fd5e6263&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a560aca3f99b145384c2b736c2ceea1c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-92fbe09a650e62b7b6ea5d8769440e51</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770136310</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Women">
  <data key="d0">Women</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Women are individuals who may be diagnosed with gestational diabetes during pregnancy.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-12fe828372a20b6606e010f0fd5e6263</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770136310</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="OGTT">
  <data key="d0">OGTT</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">The Oral Glucose Tolerance Test (OGTT) is a standard test used to determine gestational diabetes.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-12fe828372a20b6606e010f0fd5e6263</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770136310</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="100 g OGTT">
  <data key="d0">100 g OGTT</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">The 100 g OGTT is an alternative testing method for screening gestational diabetes mellitus.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-12fe828372a20b6606e010f0fd5e6263</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770136310</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Dr Gerald Reaven">
  <data key="d0">Dr Gerald Reaven</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Dr Gerald Reaven is a physician who named the cluster of symptoms related to the metabolic syndrome Syndrome X.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-12fe828372a20b6606e010f0fd5e6263</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770136311</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Metabolic Syndrome">
  <data key="d0">Metabolic Syndrome</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Metabolic syndrome refers to a cluster of conditions, including insulin resistance, that increase the risk for cardiovascular disease.&lt;SEP&gt;Metabolic syndrome is a cluster of cardiovascular risk factors often found in individuals with abnormal glucose tolerance.&lt;SEP&gt;Metabolic syndrome is a cluster of conditions, including high blood pressure, high blood sugar, and abnormal cholesterol levels, increasing the risk of heart disease and diabetes.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-12fe828372a20b6606e010f0fd5e6263&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-42a410eaaaed4b7428f5e95a4c7c4580&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e8e236a5eba0e1dbf843d32e509da045</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770136311</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Obesity">
  <data key="d0">Obesity</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Obesity is a significant risk factor for the development of type 2 diabetes in children and has seen a rapid increase in recent decades.&lt;SEP&gt;Obesity is a medical condition involving excessive body fat, which significantly increases the risk of various health issues, including cardiovascular diseases.&lt;SEP&gt;Obesity is a significant health issue that can aggravate dyslipidaemia and hypertension in patients with type 2 diabetes mellitus.&lt;SEP&gt;Obesity, particularly abdominal obesity, is a significant factor linked to the increased risk of atherosclerosis in individuals with diabetes.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-12fe828372a20b6606e010f0fd5e6263&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8e3bf51a75faa8eb6fe5fe7a0e509efe&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a07cef05efd947a538701b4c41b162b1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-eb0252816f7fbee4c50f79ef3ee56063</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770136311</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Insulin Resistance">
  <data key="d0">Insulin Resistance</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Insulin resistance is a condition where the body's cells do not respond effectively to insulin, often leading to type 2 diabetes and associated with conditions like polycystic ovarian syndrome.&lt;SEP&gt;Insulin resistance is a metabolic condition where the body's cells become less responsive to insulin, contributing to increased cardiovascular risk.&lt;SEP&gt;Insulin resistance is a condition where body cells do not respond effectively to insulin, often found in individuals with type 2 diabetes.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-12fe828372a20b6606e010f0fd5e6263&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-eb1bc7614fcd68decf9461b3b6290e95&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a07cef05efd947a538701b4c41b162b1</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770136311</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="α-Glucosidase Inhibitors">
  <data key="d0">α-Glucosidase Inhibitors</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">α-glucosidase inhibitors are oral agents that delay carbohydrate absorption in the body.&lt;SEP&gt;α-Glucosidase inhibitors are a class of medications that delay carbohydrate absorption, with acarbose and miglitol as examples.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-453e4228f98ddea76e07ce405d13fd32&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-eb0252816f7fbee4c50f79ef3ee56063</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770136311</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Acarbose">
  <data key="d0">Acarbose</data>
  <data key="d1">medication</data>
  <data key="d2">Acarbose is an α-glucosidase inhibitor used in dosages of 100–300 mg/day to delay carbohydrate absorption.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-453e4228f98ddea76e07ce405d13fd32</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770136311</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Miglitol">
  <data key="d0">Miglitol</data>
  <data key="d1">medication</data>
  <data key="d2">Miglitol is an α-glucosidase inhibitor taken in dosages of 100–300 mg/day to delay carbohydrate absorption.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-453e4228f98ddea76e07ce405d13fd32</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770136311</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Insulin">
  <data key="d0">Insulin</data>
  <data key="d1">hormone</data>
  <data key="d2">Insulin is a hormone produced by the pancreas that regulates blood glucose levels, critical for individuals with diabetes.&lt;SEP&gt;Insulin is a hormone used in diabetes management with various onset times, peak action durations, and types such as short-acting, intermediate-acting, and long-acting.&lt;SEP&gt;Insulin is a hormone used in diabetes management that has consistent effects on lowering triglycerides in poorly controlled patients.&lt;SEP&gt;Insulin is a hormone used in therapy for diabetes, helping to regulate blood sugar levels and prevent conditions like hypoglycaemia.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-453e4228f98ddea76e07ce405d13fd32&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-21112bd6ed1fe7896dbf55a52bc45a2d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ed87909b4bdb657354ca0eab1450156f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-92fbe09a650e62b7b6ea5d8769440e51</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770136312</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="NPH">
  <data key="d0">NPH</data>
  <data key="d1">medication</data>
  <data key="d2">NPH, also known as neutral protamine Hagedorn, is an intermediate-acting insulin that is used in diabetes management.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-453e4228f98ddea76e07ce405d13fd32</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770136312</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Lispro">
  <data key="d0">Lispro</data>
  <data key="d1">medication</data>
  <data key="d2">Lispro is a fast-acting insulin analog that has an onset of action of 5–15 minutes.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-453e4228f98ddea76e07ce405d13fd32</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770136312</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Aspart">
  <data key="d0">Aspart</data>
  <data key="d1">medication</data>
  <data key="d2">Aspart is another fast-acting insulin analog used in diabetes management with an onset of action of 5–15 minutes.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-453e4228f98ddea76e07ce405d13fd32</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770136313</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Glargine">
  <data key="d0">Glargine</data>
  <data key="d1">medication</data>
  <data key="d2">Glargine is a long-acting insulin analog characterized by no peak and a duration of 24 hours.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-453e4228f98ddea76e07ce405d13fd32</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770136313</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Multidisciplinary Mini Clinics">
  <data key="d0">Multidisciplinary Mini Clinics</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Multidisciplinary mini clinics provide team care involving physicians, nurses, dieticians, and health educators for improved diabetes management outcomes.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-453e4228f98ddea76e07ce405d13fd32</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770136313</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Ramadan Fasting">
  <data key="d0">Ramadan Fasting</data>
  <data key="d1">event</data>
  <data key="d2">Ramadan fasting refers to the practice where individuals abstain from eating during daylight hours; however, it poses risks for diabetic patients, especially type 1 and poorly-controlled type 2 patients.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-453e4228f98ddea76e07ce405d13fd32</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770136313</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Metformin">
  <data key="d0">Metformin</data>
  <data key="d1">medication</data>
  <data key="d2">Metformin is a biguanide used as an insulin sensitizer to decrease hepatic glucose production and improve insulin sensitivity.&lt;SEP&gt;Metformin is an oral agent recommended for type 2 diabetes management, associated with a lower risk of hypoglycemia.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-453e4228f98ddea76e07ce405d13fd32&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-eb0252816f7fbee4c50f79ef3ee56063</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770136314</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Thiazolidinediones">
  <data key="d0">Thiazolidinediones</data>
  <data key="d1">medication</data>
  <data key="d2">Thiazolidinediones, such as rosiglitazone and pioglitazone, are used to increase insulin sensitivity in diabetic patients.&lt;SEP&gt;Thiazolidinediones are oral medications preferred for type 2 diabetes management due to their lower risk of hypoglycemia.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-453e4228f98ddea76e07ce405d13fd32&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-eb0252816f7fbee4c50f79ef3ee56063</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770136314</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Short-Acting Insulin">
  <data key="d0">Short-Acting Insulin</data>
  <data key="d1">medication</data>
  <data key="d2">Short-acting insulin, such as regular and semilente, is used in diabetes management with specific onset and duration times.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-453e4228f98ddea76e07ce405d13fd32</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770136314</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Intermediate-Acting Insulin">
  <data key="d0">Intermediate-Acting Insulin</data>
  <data key="d1">medication</data>
  <data key="d2">Intermediate-acting insulin, exemplified by NPH and lente, has set onset and duration times in diabetes treatment.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-453e4228f98ddea76e07ce405d13fd32</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770136314</data>
