<node id="Type 2 Diabetes Mellitus">
  <data key="d0">Type 2 Diabetes Mellitus</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Type 2 Diabetes Mellitus is the most prevalent form of diabetes, particularly noted for its rising incidence among younger populations in various regions, including the Eastern Mediterranean. It is characterized primarily by insulin resistance, which leads to difficulties in insulin action and secretion. This condition often arises as a consequence of obesity and is significantly influenced by lifestyle factors.

While Type 2 diabetes may not always require insulin therapy for metabolic control, it is critical for individuals with this condition to engage in regular screening and effective management due to the potential long-term health implications. The increasing diagnosis of Type 2 diabetes in children and adolescents highlights the urgent need for awareness and preventive measures.

Lifestyle modifications, including improvements in diet and exercise, play a crucial role in preventing the onset of Type 2 diabetes mellitus. Health interventions aimed at promoting these changes can be effective in mitigating the risk associated with this common form of diabetes. Overall, Type 2 Diabetes Mellitus represents a significant public health challenge that necessitates ongoing monitoring and management.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-12fe828372a20b6606e010f0fd5e6263&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-56d9ff3515afac60e7566e41837249a0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5384df975133ef2a52113cd3ca0f897e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-42a410eaaaed4b7428f5e95a4c7c4580&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-92fbe09a650e62b7b6ea5d8769440e51&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1b7df1782c359efe079f6ade12b3688f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-25fb88c8ed14936954356d104de095d4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-eb0252816f7fbee4c50f79ef3ee56063</data>
