  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Impaired Fasting Glycaemia (IFG) denotes a condition where fasting glucose levels are abnormal but do not meet the criteria for diabetes diagnosis.&lt;SEP&gt;Impaired fasting glycaemia describes a clinical stage where fasting glucose levels are elevated but not diagnostic of diabetes.</data>
