<node id="Dyslipidaemia">
  <data key="d0">Dyslipidaemia</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Dyslipidaemia is a medical condition characterized by abnormal levels of lipids in the blood, which is particularly significant in the context of diabetes management and overall patient care. It is often associated with elevated triglycerides and low high-density lipoprotein (HDL) cholesterol, making it a common feature in diabetic patients. 

The condition entails not only the presence of abnormal lipid levels but also requires healthcare providers to rule out secondary causes. This is crucial for establishing an accurate diagnosis and ensuring appropriate treatment. The management of dyslipidaemia often includes lifestyle changes, such as dietary modifications and increased physical activity, along with potential medical therapies to control lipid levels effectively.

Dyslipidaemia is particularly relevant because it is linked to increased risks of cardiovascular diseases, complicating the health profiles of those with diabetes. Therefore, careful management of lipid levels is essential in reducing these risks and enhancing patient outcomes.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-12fe828372a20b6606e010f0fd5e6263&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a560aca3f99b145384c2b736c2ceea1c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8361af576f7e73b0bd2ea813976f60b3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-21112bd6ed1fe7896dbf55a52bc45a2d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ed87909b4bdb657354ca0eab1450156f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1b7df1782c359efe079f6ade12b3688f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a07cef05efd947a538701b4c41b162b1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-eb0252816f7fbee4c50f79ef3ee56063</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770136317</data>
