<node id="Hypertension">
  <data key="d0">Hypertension</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Hypertension is a medical condition characterized by persistently elevated blood pressure. This condition significantly increases the risk of cardiovascular disease and is often associated with other health issues such as type 2 diabetes and metabolic syndrome. If left untreated, hypertension can lead to serious complications, including increased cardiovascular mortality and the progression of kidney disease.

The condition necessitates careful management, particularly in individuals with diabetes, as it can complicate diabetes treatment and contribute to related complications such as nephropathy and retinopathy. Management strategies for hypertension typically include lifestyle modifications and medication options, with commonly prescribed treatments being thiazide diuretics and ACE inhibitors. 

Furthermore, hypertension is not only a risk factor for cardiovascular disease but may also influence the severity of diabetes and its related conditions. Overall, effective control of high blood pressure is crucial for reducing health risks and ensuring the well-being of individuals affected by this condition.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-12fe828372a20b6606e010f0fd5e6263&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-453e4228f98ddea76e07ce405d13fd32&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a560aca3f99b145384c2b736c2ceea1c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c4d75b2c01d2448f37de4deec12208fa&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-eb1bc7614fcd68decf9461b3b6290e95&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a07cef05efd947a538701b4c41b162b1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5e1400e1158e4f7be2283a0366ebf4f2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e8e236a5eba0e1dbf843d32e509da045&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-fd4cfbed43aa26af0eef694fecac2177</data>
