<node id="Nephropathy">
  <data key="d0">Nephropathy</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Nephropathy is a kidney-related complication of diabetes that can lead to kidney failure.&lt;SEP&gt;Nephropathy is kidney disease that commonly occurs in diabetic patients and can lead to renal failure if not managed properly.&lt;SEP&gt;Nephropathy is a complication of diabetes that affects the kidneys and can impact the management and treatment of foot disorders.&lt;SEP&gt;Nephropathy is a kidney condition that requires special attention during angiography, especially when patients are in early stages.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-56d9ff3515afac60e7566e41837249a0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5e1400e1158e4f7be2283a0366ebf4f2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e8e236a5eba0e1dbf843d32e509da045&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-55d2691a8c714949752d249721fec5e7</data>
