<node id="Type 1 Diabetes Mellitus">
  <data key="d0">Type 1 Diabetes Mellitus</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Type 1 diabetes is a form of diabetes that requires insulin for survival, often resulting from autoimmune destruction of pancreatic islet β-cells.&lt;SEP&gt;Type 1 Diabetes is characterized by the destruction of insulin-producing beta cells, requiring insulin for survival.&lt;SEP&gt;Type 1 diabetes mellitus is a form of diabetes common in brittle diabetes, where the body cannot produce insulin.&lt;SEP&gt;Type 1 diabetes mellitus is a condition that arises when the immune system attacks insulin-producing cells in the pancreas.&lt;SEP&gt;Type 1 diabetes mellitus currently has no definitive prevention methods, though research continues.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-56d9ff3515afac60e7566e41837249a0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-42a410eaaaed4b7428f5e95a4c7c4580&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-92fbe09a650e62b7b6ea5d8769440e51&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1b7df1782c359efe079f6ade12b3688f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-25fb88c8ed14936954356d104de095d4</data>
