<node id="Distal Symmetrical Sensory-Motor Polyneuropathy">
  <data key="d0">Distal Symmetrical Sensory-Motor Polyneuropathy</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Distal symmetrical sensory-motor polyneuropathy is a common form of neuropathy divided into three stages: early, symptomatic, and severe.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-0748670b42b0f4e0b2ed9c5ce62d54e7</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770136321</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Hyperglycaemia">
  <data key="d0">Hyperglycaemia</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Hyperglycaemia is a condition characterized by elevated blood glucose levels, significant in the context of metabolic syndrome and diabetes management.&lt;SEP&gt;Hyperglycaemia is a condition associated with diabetes that can lead to notable complications such as atherosclerosis.&lt;SEP&gt;Hyperglycaemia is associated with diabetes and affects nerve structure through various potential mechanisms.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-0748670b42b0f4e0b2ed9c5ce62d54e7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8e3bf51a75faa8eb6fe5fe7a0e509efe&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e8e236a5eba0e1dbf843d32e509da045</data>
