</node>
<node id="Diabetic Neuropathy">
  <data key="d0">Diabetic Neuropathy</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Diabetic neuropathy is a common microvascular complication of diabetes mellitus that can lead to significant morbidity.&lt;SEP&gt;Diabetic neuropathy is a type of nerve damage occurring in patients with diabetes, impacting their ability to feel pain and touch.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-0748670b42b0f4e0b2ed9c5ce62d54e7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-55d2691a8c714949752d249721fec5e7</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770136321</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Cardiovascular Autonomic Neuropathy">
  <data key="d0">Cardiovascular Autonomic Neuropathy</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Cardiovascular autonomic neuropathy is a type of neuropathy that affects heart rate control and can lead to increased mortality risk.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-0748670b42b0f4e0b2ed9c5ce62d54e7</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770136321</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Aldose Reductase Inhibitors">
  <data key="d0">Aldose Reductase Inhibitors</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Aldose reductase inhibitors are drugs that have the potential to inhibit the polyol pathway associated with diabetic neuropathy.&lt;SEP&gt;Aldose reductase inhibitors are therapeutic agents under investigation for their potential benefits in treating neuropathy.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-0748670b42b0f4e0b2ed9c5ce62d54e7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-55d2691a8c714949752d249721fec5e7</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770136321</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
