</node>
<node id="Glycaemic Control">
  <data key="d0">Glycaemic Control</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Glycaemic control refers to the management of blood glucose levels in individuals with diabetes to prevent complications and long-term health issues.&lt;SEP&gt;Glycaemic control is the management of blood glucose levels to minimize the development and progression of diabetic neuropathy.&lt;SEP&gt;Glycaemic control refers to the management of blood glucose levels in diabetic patients to prevent complications like neuropathy.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-0748670b42b0f4e0b2ed9c5ce62d54e7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e8e236a5eba0e1dbf843d32e509da045&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-55d2691a8c714949752d249721fec5e7</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770136322</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Severe Distal Sensory-Motor Neuropathy">
  <data key="d0">Severe Distal Sensory-Motor Neuropathy</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Severe distal sensory-motor neuropathy is a stage of neuropathy characterized by motor involvement and potential for ulceration and severe symptoms.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-0748670b42b0f4e0b2ed9c5ce62d54e7</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770136322</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Symptomatic Distal Sensory-Motor Neuropathy">
  <data key="d0">Symptomatic Distal Sensory-Motor Neuropathy</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Symptomatic distal sensory-motor neuropathy is a stage characterized by sensory loss and may also include paraesthesia and pain.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-0748670b42b0f4e0b2ed9c5ce62d54e7</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770136322</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Early Distal Sensory-Motor Neuropathy">
  <data key="d0">Early Distal Sensory-Motor Neuropathy</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Early distal sensory-motor neuropathy is typically asymptomatic but can have detectable sensory abnormalities through testing.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-0748670b42b0f4e0b2ed9c5ce62d54e7</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770136322</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Ulceration">
  <data key="d0">Ulceration</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Ulceration refers to a possible severe consequence of neuropathy that can lead to infection, necrosis, and gangrene.</data>
