<node id="Meal Patterns">
  <data key="d0">Meal Patterns</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Meal patterns are patterns of food intake that may influence blood glucose levels and overall diabetes management.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e5fc5e661d0f94cc23c0188b9bbe4e08</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770136323</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Acute Complications">
  <data key="d0">Acute Complications</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Acute complications refer to immediate health risks associated with diabetes, such as infection, hypoglycemia, or ketoacidosis.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e5fc5e661d0f94cc23c0188b9bbe4e08</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770136323</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Chronic Complications">
  <data key="d0">Chronic Complications</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Chronic complications are long-term health issues related to diabetes, including effects on vision, kidney function, and cardiovascular health.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e5fc5e661d0f94cc23c0188b9bbe4e08</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770136324</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Lifestyle and Psychosocial Elements">
  <data key="d0">Lifestyle and Psychosocial Elements</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Lifestyle and psychosocial elements are factors that can affect diabetes management and should be considered during patient evaluations.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e5fc5e661d0f94cc23c0188b9bbe4e08</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770136324</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Type 2 Diabetes">
  <data key="d0">Type 2 Diabetes</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Type 2 diabetes is a metabolic disorder resulting from insulin resistance, increasingly diagnosed in younger populations in the Eastern Mediterranean.&lt;SEP&gt;Type 2 Diabetes is a common form of diabetes that usually arises at a relatively young age in certain populations.&lt;SEP&gt;Type 2 diabetes is a chronic condition characterized by insulin resistance, leading to elevated blood glucose levels and potential complications.&lt;SEP&gt;Type 2 diabetes is a chronic condition affecting the way the body metabolizes sugar, resulting in high blood glucose levels.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-c4d75b2c01d2448f37de4deec12208fa&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d8c827cc2249067692290d6a8a0e8018&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-eb1bc7614fcd68decf9461b3b6290e95&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f15f59b3ff05825a61f252ed8f9a74e1</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770136324</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Da Quing Study">
  <data key="d0">Da Quing Study</data>
  <data key="d1">event</data>
  <data key="d2">The Da Quing Study is a research project in China that demonstrated the effectiveness of diet and exercise in reducing the risk of type 2 diabetes.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-c4d75b2c01d2448f37de4deec12208fa</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770136324</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
