<node id="HDL Cholesterol">
  <data key="d0">HDL Cholesterol</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">HDL Cholesterol is known as "good" cholesterol; higher levels are generally associated with lower risk of heart disease.&lt;SEP&gt;HDL cholesterol is a type of cholesterol that can be raised through medication and is associated with reduced heart disease risk.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-8361af576f7e73b0bd2ea813976f60b3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-21112bd6ed1fe7896dbf55a52bc45a2d</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770136325</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Statins">
  <data key="d0">Statins</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Statins are a class of medications used to lower LDL cholesterol and triglycerides while raising HDL cholesterol.&lt;SEP&gt;Statins are a class of drugs used as first-line therapy for lowering cholesterol levels, particularly in patients intolerant to other treatments.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-8361af576f7e73b0bd2ea813976f60b3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-21112bd6ed1fe7896dbf55a52bc45a2d</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770136325</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Bile Acid Sequestrants">
  <data key="d0">Bile Acid Sequestrants</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Bile Acid Sequestrants are second-line medications used to lower LDL cholesterol, often in combination with statins.</data>
