<node id="Hypoglycaemia">
  <data key="d0">Hypoglycaemia</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Hypoglycaemia occurs when blood glucose levels drop significantly low; it is a common symptom in brittle diabetes.&lt;SEP&gt;Hypoglycaemia refers to a condition where blood sugar levels drop significantly, leading to symptoms that require recognition and management, particularly in insulin-treated patients.&lt;SEP&gt;Hypoglycaemia is a medical condition marked by abnormally low blood glucose levels, which can occur in individuals with diabetes treated with insulin or hypoglycaemic medications.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ed87909b4bdb657354ca0eab1450156f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-76910bb9e0e5a60b043dd2786bf63e97&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1b7df1782c359efe079f6ade12b3688f</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770136332</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Reye Syndrome">
  <data key="d0">Reye Syndrome</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Reye syndrome is a serious condition associated with aspirin use in children, leading to acute liver and brain dysfunction.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ed87909b4bdb657354ca0eab1450156f</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770136332</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
