<node id="Primary Prevention of Diabetes">
  <data key="d0">Primary Prevention of Diabetes</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Primary prevention of diabetes involves strategies aimed at preventing the onset of diabetes and minimizing the need for care and treatment of complications.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-2173942c84747feba52cff952903a7f5</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770136335</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Screening for Type 2 Diabetes Mellitus">
  <data key="d0">Screening for Type 2 Diabetes Mellitus</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Screening for type 2 diabetes mellitus focuses on the early identification of individuals at risk, which is essential for prevention.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-2173942c84747feba52cff952903a7f5</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770136335</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Regional Training Course for Diabetes Educators">
  <data key="d0">Regional Training Course for Diabetes Educators</data>
  <data key="d1">event</data>
  <data key="d2">The regional training course for diabetes educators aims to provide essential training and integration of best practices in diabetes care.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-2173942c84747feba52cff952903a7f5</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770136335</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Development of a National Strategy">
  <data key="d0">Development of a National Strategy</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">The development of a national strategy for diabetes management requires implementation plans to monitor and control diabetes, hypertension, dyslipidaemia, and obesity.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-2173942c84747feba52cff952903a7f5</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770136335</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Insulin Treatment">
  <data key="d0">Insulin Treatment</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Insulin treatment is a medical approach used by patients with diabetes to manage their blood glucose levels, requiring careful monitoring and adjustment.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-76910bb9e0e5a60b043dd2786bf63e97</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770136335</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Ketoacidosis">
  <data key="d0">Ketoacidosis</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Ketoacidosis is a severe complication of diabetes mainly affecting individuals with type 1 diabetes, characterized by an excess of ketones in the body leading to acidosis and potentially death.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-76910bb9e0e5a60b043dd2786bf63e97&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-42a410eaaaed4b7428f5e95a4c7c4580</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770136336</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Blood Glucose Monitoring">
  <data key="d0">Blood Glucose Monitoring</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Blood glucose monitoring involves regularly checking blood sugar levels to manage and prevent complications in diabetes patients.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-76910bb9e0e5a60b043dd2786bf63e97</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770136336</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Emergency Medical Personnel">
  <data key="d0">Emergency Medical Personnel</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Emergency medical personnel are healthcare providers who must be familiar with the recognition and management of conditions like hypoglycaemia and ketoacidosis in patients.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-76910bb9e0e5a60b043dd2786bf63e97</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770136336</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Family Members">
  <data key="d0">Family Members</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Family members of diabetic patients are important in supporting the management and emergency treatment of conditions like hypoglycaemia.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-76910bb9e0e5a60b043dd2786bf63e97</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770136336</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Chronic Diabetes Complications">
  <data key="d0">Chronic Diabetes Complications</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Chronic diabetes complications are long-term health issues that can arise from poorly managed diabetes, affecting various body systems over time.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-76910bb9e0e5a60b043dd2786bf63e97</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770136336</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Sulfonylureas">
  <data key="d0">Sulfonylureas</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Sulfonylureas are a class of insulin secretagogues used to stimulate insulin secretion in diabetic patients.&lt;SEP&gt;Sulfonylureas are a class of medications used to increase insulin production in patients with type 2 diabetes, which can lead to hypoglycaemia if not managed properly.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-76910bb9e0e5a60b043dd2786bf63e97&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-eb0252816f7fbee4c50f79ef3ee56063</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770136336</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Impaired Glucose Regulation">
  <data key="d0">Impaired Glucose Regulation</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Impaired glucose regulation refers to a stage between normoglycemia and diabetes which can indicate an increased risk for developing diabetes.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-92fbe09a650e62b7b6ea5d8769440e51</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770136336</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Malnutrition-Related Diabetes">
  <data key="d0">Malnutrition-Related Diabetes</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Malnutrition-related diabetes (MRDM) was a classification of diabetes influenced by nutritional factors, which has been recommended for deletion.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-92fbe09a650e62b7b6ea5d8769440e51</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770136337</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Cystic Fibrosis">
  <data key="d0">Cystic Fibrosis</data>
  <data key="d1">condition</data>
  <data key="d2">Cystic fibrosis is an inherited condition that affects the respiratory and digestive systems and can lead to diabetes due to pancreatic dysfunction.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-92fbe09a650e62b7b6ea5d8769440e51</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770136337</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Epidemicity Index">
  <data key="d0">Epidemicity Index</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">The epidemicity index is a proposed measure of the relationship between the prevalence of impaired glucose tolerance and diabetes mellitus in a population.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-92fbe09a650e62b7b6ea5d8769440e51</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770136337</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Insulin-Dependent Diabetes Mellitus">
  <data key="d0">Insulin-Dependent Diabetes Mellitus</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Insulin-dependent diabetes mellitus (IDDM) is an older term for type 1 diabetes that is no longer recommended for use due to potential confusion.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-92fbe09a650e62b7b6ea5d8769440e51</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770136337</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Non-Insulin-Dependent Diabetes Mellitus">
  <data key="d0">Non-Insulin-Dependent Diabetes Mellitus</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Non-insulin-dependent diabetes mellitus (NIDDM) is an older term for type 2 diabetes that is not recommended for use as it can lead to misclassification.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-92fbe09a650e62b7b6ea5d8769440e51</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770136337</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Hypothyroidism">
  <data key="d0">Hypothyroidism</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Hypothyroidism is a condition that may contribute to dyslipidaemia, characterized by insufficient thyroid hormone production.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1b7df1782c359efe079f6ade12b3688f</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770136337</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Obstructive Liver Disease">
  <data key="d0">Obstructive Liver Disease</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Obstructive liver disease is a possible cause of dyslipidaemia, affecting liver function.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1b7df1782c359efe079f6ade12b3688f</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770136337</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Chronic Renal Disease">
  <data key="d0">Chronic Renal Disease</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Chronic renal disease may lead to dyslipidaemia and involves tests like urinalysis and creatinine clearance.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1b7df1782c359efe079f6ade12b3688f</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770136337</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Brittle Diabetes">
  <data key="d0">Brittle Diabetes</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Brittle diabetes is a variant of diabetes mellitus characterized by unstable blood glucose levels despite management efforts.&lt;SEP&gt;Brittle diabetes is a form of diabetes characterized by extreme fluctuations in blood glucose levels, often causing management difficulties.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1b7df1782c359efe079f6ade12b3688f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a07cef05efd947a538701b4c41b162b1</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770136337</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Diabetic Ketoacidosis">
  <data key="d0">Diabetic Ketoacidosis</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Diabetic ketoacidosis is a severe complication of diabetes characterized by high blood sugars and ketones.&lt;SEP&gt;Diabetic ketoacidosis is a severe complication of diabetes that can be precipitated by infections and requires prompt treatment.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1b7df1782c359efe079f6ade12b3688f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8e3bf51a75faa8eb6fe5fe7a0e509efe</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770136337</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Population Screening">
  <data key="d0">Population Screening</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Population screening is a method for identifying diabetes in community settings, especially for health planning.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1b7df1782c359efe079f6ade12b3688f</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770136337</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Selective Screening">
  <data key="d0">Selective Screening</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Selective screening targets specific populations at risk for type 2 diabetes to identify cases effectively.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1b7df1782c359efe079f6ade12b3688f</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770136337</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Opportunistic Screening">
  <data key="d0">Opportunistic Screening</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Opportunistic screening occurs when high-risk individuals seek healthcare, capitalizing on existing system interactions.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1b7df1782c359efe079f6ade12b3688f</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770136338</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Screening Protocol">
  <data key="d0">Screening Protocol</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Screening protocol involves guidelines and procedures to reduce the adverse effects of screening for diabetes.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1b7df1782c359efe079f6ade12b3688f</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770136338</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Impaired Glucose Tolerance (IGT)">
  <data key="d0">Impaired Glucose Tolerance (IGT)</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Impaired Glucose Tolerance (IGT) refers to a pre-diabetic state where blood sugar levels are higher than normal, affecting numerous individuals in the Region.&lt;SEP&gt;Impaired glucose tolerance (IGT) is a condition that is often undiagnosed and may be identified through screening methods for diabetes.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1b7df1782c359efe079f6ade12b3688f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f15f59b3ff05825a61f252ed8f9a74e1</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770136338</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Diabetic Individuals">
  <data key="d0">Diabetic Individuals</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Diabetic individuals are those who have diabetes and are more prone to infections and complications compared to non-diabetics.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-8e3bf51a75faa8eb6fe5fe7a0e509efe</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770136338</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Bladder">
  <data key="d0">Bladder</data>
  <data key="d1">naturalobject</data>
  <data key="d2">The bladder is an organ affected by diabetes, with urinary tract infections being more common in diabetic patients.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-8e3bf51a75faa8eb6fe5fe7a0e509efe</data>
