<node id="Retinopathy">
  <data key="d0">Retinopathy</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Retinopathy is a diabetes-related complication that affects the eyes and can lead to blindness if not managed properly.&lt;SEP&gt;Diabetic retinopathy is a significant complication of diabetes, leading to blindness and visual impairment in adults.&lt;SEP&gt;Retinopathy refers to damage to the retina, often linked with diabetes, that can threaten vision and may be asymptomatic in early stages.&lt;SEP&gt;Retinopathy is a sight-threatening condition that can lead to blindness, characterized by damage to the retina, often without symptoms in early stages.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-8e3bf51a75faa8eb6fe5fe7a0e509efe&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7ef79f22f40772c2060b439008ce485b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5e1400e1158e4f7be2283a0366ebf4f2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e8e236a5eba0e1dbf843d32e509da045</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770136338</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Young-Onset Type 1 Diabetes">
  <data key="d0">Young-Onset Type 1 Diabetes</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Young-onset type 1 diabetes is a form of diabetes diagnosed at a young age, leading to a high risk of developing diabetic retinopathy.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-8e3bf51a75faa8eb6fe5fe7a0e509efe</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770136339</data>
