  <data key="d2">Linearly independent columns are those columns in a matrix that cannot be expressed as linear combinations of other columns, essential for solutions.&lt;SEP&gt;Linearly independent columns refer to a set of columns in a matrix where no column can be expressed as a linear combination of others, which is crucial for unique solutions in linear algebra.</data>
