<node id="Machine Learning">
  <data key="d0">Machine Learning</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Machine learning is a technique within artificial intelligence that allows computers to learn from data and improve outcomes without explicit programming.&lt;SEP&gt;Machine learning is an approach that can discover mappings from representations to outputs and also learn the representations themselves.&lt;SEP&gt;Machine learning is a subset of AI that focuses on systems improving with experience and data without being explicitly programmed.&lt;SEP&gt;Machine learning is a field of artificial intelligence that involves the development of algorithms and statistical models that enable computers to perform tasks without explicit instructions.&lt;SEP&gt;Machine learning involves specifications of models that represent beliefs and the use of algorithms to achieve defined goals.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-d052846d3bce5d76b5380e3fe4a4925e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-24b6e16206da653229333e2acff91797&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2aff4303e41c5babfaf2c4d7bf68299d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-010a987a088000cbaebd51b9889052f3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bd2a057016fddbfc53fb1a5ab4973351&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a141800f1c44ebc302d730822f4d8c41</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1770136819</data>
