<node id="Connectionism">
  <data key="d0">Connectionism</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Connectionism is a theoretical approach to understanding how mental phenomena can be described by interconnected networks of simple units.&lt;SEP&gt;Connectionism is a theoretical framework in cognitive science that focuses on how networks of simple computational units can produce intelligent behavior through neural implementations.&lt;SEP&gt;Connectionism is a theory in cognitive science that models mental or behavioral phenomena as the emergent processes of interconnected networks of simple units.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-cd0905a2bbd4a2e98ea5834719f28254&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-24b6e16206da653229333e2acff91797&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3e301584dbc493504e638dde9613d0a9</data>
