<node id="L1 Norm">
  <data key="d0">L1 Norm</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">L1 norm refers to the sum of the absolute values of the components of a vector, commonly used in various mathematical and machine learning contexts.&lt;SEP&gt;The L1 Norm is a mathematical concept used to represent the number of non-zero entries in a vector, which remains unchanged when the vector is scaled.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-0403607cb7181d4a13a232d13fec9630&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e325d64a50359748cfb47987a361fbb1</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
